description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time to be working at the Royal Free London NHS Foundation Trust, one of the biggest NHS Trusts in the UK, delivering care to more than 1.6 million people a year through our three main hospitals: Barnet, Chase Farm and Royal Free. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We are looking for a Band 7 Pain Management Physiotherapist to work within our established Multidisciplinary Pain Team. The post will involve managing a caseload of complex patients, clinical supervision and service development at the Royal Free Hospital, Hampstead site and at our Pain Management Department in Edgware Community Hospital. The Pain team is a friendly dynamic team that encourages and supports ongoing professional development.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will be working alongside clinical lead physiotherapist and team of pain management physiotherapists to help with current ongoing service development. The Band 7 role also carries an important education component. You will be expected to participate in the teaching and training of more junior staff and lecturing to other health care professionals as appropriate. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Suitable applicants would be expected to have significant experience within the pain management field and relevant master’s level, or equivalent, post-graduate study.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you believe you meet the criteria of the person specification and would like to join the Royal Free at this time, we would be interested in receiving your application.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Craig Crawley&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Advanced Physiotherapy Practitioner and Pain Physiotherapy Lead.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: craig.crawley@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
